    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 138 
                    The Ambassador in the United Kingdom (
                        Winant
                    ) to the Acting Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d138</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">138</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-13T09:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-13T09:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-13T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-13T09:00:00-05:00" n="138" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss>/7–1345:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 138 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJG2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent—<gloss target="#t_Niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-13T16:00:00+02:00">July 13, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7072. Press correspondents in London say have received word from their Washington
                    offices that in closing days of Big Three Conference a rendezvous somewhere on
                    continent will be fixed for correspondents from here whence they may go to join
                    President’s party. Correspondents claim Washington sources also say Embassy in
                    London will notify them of time and place for rendezvous.</p>
                <p>We have no record of any instructions on this point. Please instruct that we may
                    deal with such inquiries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
